<h1>Eligibility</h1>
<br />
<p>The Idaho Work Study Program is open to Idaho residents who have an off campus job related to their field of study.</p>
<p>The student must:</p>
<ul>
<li>Be a current BYU-Idaho student</li>
<li>Be enrolled in at least 6 credits</li>
<li>Be working 20 hours per week or less</li>
<li>Have achieved <a href="x40183.xml" title="Satisfactory Academic Progress" target="_blank">Satisfactory Academic Progress (SAP) standards</a></li>
<li>Have employment that is directly related to the student&rsquo;s field of study</li>
</ul>
<h3>Residency</h3>
<p>In order to be considered an Idaho resident, the student must be one of the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>A graduate of an accredited high school in the State of Idaho If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us.</li>
<li>A dependent whose parent or guardian qualifies as an Idaho State resident</li>
<li>A spouse of a person who is an Idaho State resident</li>
<li>If you do not meet one of the above items, you may be an Idaho resident based on other criteria, found in Title 33 Section 33-3717B.</li>
</ul>
<p><a href="Documents/Admin_Offices/Financial Aid/Idaho Work Study/IdahoResidencyForm.pdf" title="Idaho Residency Form" target="_blank">Student Residency Application Form</a></p>
<ul></ul>
<h3>Forms</h3>
<p>If you meet these requirements and would like to be a part of the Idaho Work Study program, fill out the following forms and fax or turn it in to the Financial Aid Office.</p>
